The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 PCB hearing 

Karachi: Head of the appellate tribunal, hearing the plea of fast bowlers Shoaib Akhtar and Mohammed Asif against their doping bans, said on Tuesday that a final decision was possible shortly. 

The tribunal held a long hearing for the second day running in Lahore on Tuesday before handing out a questionnaire to the lawyers of both players. Mark Gay, barrister at law, had appeared on behalf of the PCB and made his final submission. (PTI) 




